TY  - JOUR
T1  - Why Do Firms Reduce Business Risk?
AU  - Amit, Raphael
AU  - Wernerfelt, Birger
Y1  - 1990/09/01
PY  - 1990
DA  - 1990/09/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/256579
DO  - 10.5465/256579
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 520
EP  - 533
VL  - 33
IS  - 3
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - Two empirical tests designed to disentangle firms' motives for reducing business risk were performed. Results suggest that low business risk allows firms to acquire factors of production at lower costs, to operate more efficiently, or both. These findings are consistent with theories assuming both value maximization and efficient capital markets.
AB  - Two empirical tests designed to disentangle firms' motives for reducing business risk were performed. Results suggest that low business risk allows firms to acquire factors of production at lower costs, to operate more efficiently, or both. These findings are consistent with theories assuming both value maximization and efficient capital markets.
